      "id": "PopularPost123086",
      "post_content": "An uncommon use of Lair lands like this is in a landfall deck to return lands to your hand for the purpose of replaying them. This is especially useful in tandem with cards that allow you to play additional lands in a turn, like [Oracle of Mul Daya](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Oracle of Mul Daya) or [Azusa, Lost but Seeking](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Azusa, Lost but Seeking). You can also use it to replay lands that give you a benefit when they come enter the battlefield, such as [Khalni Garden](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Khalni Garden) or [Sejiri Refuge](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sejiri Refuge) and other refuge cards. Lastly, you can use Lairs to renew counters on land cards that come into play with counters on them, like [Vivid Grove](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vivid Grove) or [Llanowar Reborn](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Llanowar Reborn).",
      "posted_by": "AssKickingBoots",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost123086\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">An uncommon use of Lair lands like this is in a landfall deck to return lands to your hand for the purpose of replaying them. This is especially useful in tandem with cards that allow you to play additional lands in a turn, like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Oracle of Mul Daya\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Oracle of Mul Daya\">Oracle of Mul Daya</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Azusa, Lost but Seeking\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Azusa, Lost but Seeking\">Azusa, Lost but Seeking</a>. You can also use it to replay lands that give you a benefit when they come enter the battlefield, such as <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Khalni Garden\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Khalni Garden\">Khalni Garden</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sejiri Refuge\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sejiri Refuge\">Sejiri Refuge</a> and other refuge cards. Lastly, you can use Lairs to renew counters on land cards that come into play with counters on them, like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Vivid Grove\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vivid Grove\">Vivid Grove</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Llanowar Reborn\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Llanowar Reborn\">Llanowar Reborn</a>.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '123086'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n      